---
// Demo proving the phase-2 pipeline end to end: a Markdown body with ::island
// directives -> renderPostBody -> hydrated interactive islands. Lives under
// /admin so it's noindex + excluded from the sitemap. Safe to delete once the
// real /blog rendering reads from the PDS.
export const prerender = true;
import Default from "../../layouts/Default.astro";
import PostBody from "../../components/PostBody.astro";

const sample = `# Hello from AT Protocol

This post body is **Markdown**, stored as a record and rendered by Astro — with
interactive *islands* embedded **by reference**, not as code.

## A focus timer

::island[pomodoro]

Above is a real Svelte component, hydrated from a Markdown directive.

## A colour swatch with props

::island[colourSwatch]{h=210 s=80 l=55}

That's the whole pipeline: \`::island[key]{props}\` resolves to a repo component.`;
---

<Default title="Post preview — admin" description="Island renderer demo">
  <meta slot="head" name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
  <main style="max-width: 60ch; margin-inline: auto;">
    <PostBody body={sample} />
  </main>
</Default>
